# animate(changes:completion:)

**Instance Method**

Animates changes using the animation in the current transaction.

## Declaration

```swift
@MainActor @preconcurrency func animate(changes: () -> Void, completion: (() -> Void)? = nil)
```

## Parameters

- **changes**: A closure that changes animatable properties.
- **completion**: A closure to execute after the animation completes.

## Discussion

This combines doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/UIKit/UIView/4429628-animate with the current transaction’s animation. When you start a SwiftUI animation using [doc://com.apple.SwiftUI/documentation/SwiftUI/withAnimation(_:_:)] and have a mutated SwiftUI state that causes the representable object to update, use this method to animate changes in the representable object using the same `Animation` timing.

```swift
struct ContentView: View {
    @State private var isCollapsed = false
    var body: some View {
        ZStack {
            MyDetailView(isCollapsed: isCollapsed)
            MyRepresentable(isCollapsed: $isCollapsed)
            Button("Collapse Content") {
                withAnimation(.bouncy) {
                    isCollapsed = true
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

struct MyRepresentable: UIViewRepresentable {
    @Binding var isCollapsed: Bool

    func updateUIView(_ uiView: UIViewType, context: Context) {
        if isCollapsed && !uiView.isCollapsed {
            context.animate {
                uiView.collapseSubview()
                uiView.layout()
            }
        }
    }
}
```
